128
00:05:26,579 --> 00:05:35,000
[SPEAKER_01] even though it is not stable energy provision, it doesn't provide energy during night time or when no wind blows.

129
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:40,420
[SPEAKER_01] And we as an industrialized country, of course, need a stable energy grid.

130
00:05:41,360 --> 00:05:48,379
[SPEAKER_01] And so from topic to topic, we always proved after a certain time to be right,

131
00:05:48,379 --> 00:05:54,160
[SPEAKER_01] even though people at the beginning didn't understand us and our positions.

132
00:05:54,160 --> 00:05:58,740
[SPEAKER_01] So it was easy for the political competitors, the other parties.

133
00:05:58,740 --> 00:06:08,079
[SPEAKER_01] It was easy for the media, who are, of course, instrumentalized to keep the existing power structures in place,

134
00:06:08,220 --> 00:06:15,800
[SPEAKER_01] to demonize us as being radicals, as being ignorant of climate change, etc.,

135
00:06:15,800 --> 00:06:21,680
[SPEAKER_01] as being xenophobic, homophobic, and whatever phobic.

136
00:06:21,680 --> 00:06:27,279
[SPEAKER_01] And people tend to believe this, at least in the western parts of Germany.

137
00:06:27,279 --> 00:06:31,360
[SPEAKER_01] In the eastern parts of Germany, people think differently.

138
00:06:31,360 --> 00:06:44,120
[SPEAKER_01] They are quite independent in thinking and making up their minds because they have had gone through that experience of 40 years of GDR and bombardment with state propaganda.

139
00:06:44,120 --> 00:06:51,939
[SPEAKER_01] But in the west, people tend to think, oh, what the mainstream media tell you is totally right.

140
00:06:51,939 --> 00:06:56,779
[SPEAKER_01] And all the experts prove it and experts are real experts and are neutral.

141
00:06:56,779 --> 00:07:03,220
[SPEAKER_01] So in the west, we really had a very difficult time since, I would say, two years ago.

142
00:07:03,220 --> 00:07:13,060
[SPEAKER_01] And then our survey results started to rise really strongly over two years,

143
00:07:13,180 --> 00:07:17,459
[SPEAKER_01] just with one little valley that was created through a media hoax.

144
00:07:17,459 --> 00:07:25,240
[SPEAKER_01] They just told people, oh, we plan to deport all the foreigners, even people with German passport,

145
00:07:25,240 --> 00:07:29,319
[SPEAKER_01] but migration background, which is, of course, complete nonsense.

146
00:07:29,319 --> 00:07:31,399
[SPEAKER_01] But people believed it again.

147
00:07:31,819 --> 00:07:39,980
[SPEAKER_01] And now we went up, up, up, up, and we landed at 20.8% for this federal election now.

148
00:07:39,980 --> 00:07:46,279
[SPEAKER_01] And I feel it's not the end, but it's the beginning of people waking up,

149
00:07:46,279 --> 00:07:55,860
[SPEAKER_01] emancipating themselves from the, yeah, steered thinking, steered voting,

150
00:07:55,860 --> 00:08:01,579
[SPEAKER_01] steered by, of course, those who are in power in media and in the government.

151
00:08:01,579 --> 00:08:06,680
[SPEAKER_01] And so far, but we will be a ruling party sooner or later.

152
00:08:06,680 --> 00:08:07,959
[SPEAKER_01] That's my conviction.

153
00:08:07,959 --> 00:08:09,040
[SPEAKER_00] Okay.

154
00:08:09,040 --> 00:08:14,879
[SPEAKER_00] Just to clarify, here in Croatia, just like in the Western countries,

155
00:08:14,879 --> 00:08:18,639
[SPEAKER_00] you are presented as a dangerous party, radical party.

156
00:08:18,639 --> 00:08:23,759
[SPEAKER_00] Behind all the stories about the AFD is the fear of dark forces.

157
00:08:23,759 --> 00:08:29,839
[SPEAKER_00] We could read that Germans are afraid of returning to Hitler's settings.

158
00:08:29,839 --> 00:08:30,540
[SPEAKER_00] Yeah.

159
00:08:30,540 --> 00:08:35,700
[SPEAKER_01] This is complete nonsense.

160
00:08:35,700 --> 00:08:44,500
[SPEAKER_01] I mean, we hate the political system that Hitler had set up at those times,

161
00:08:44,500 --> 00:08:46,500
[SPEAKER_01] at those dark times of Germany.

162
00:08:46,500 --> 00:08:48,000
[SPEAKER_01] We hate the system.

163
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:50,639
[SPEAKER_01] Because what was Hitler standing for?

164
00:08:51,179 --> 00:08:56,279
[SPEAKER_01] He was standing for total control of what people think and do.

165
00:08:56,279 --> 00:08:59,720
[SPEAKER_01] And everyone should behave in the same manner.

166
00:08:59,720 --> 00:09:08,059
[SPEAKER_01] And that's what the present forces in power ask from people when there is a COVID crisis out there,

167
00:09:08,059 --> 00:09:14,340
[SPEAKER_01] which was exaggerated or maybe even created by those in power.

168
00:09:14,340 --> 00:09:32,720
[SPEAKER_01] And they abused the virus to steer people's thinking through fear and to make them obey and do whatever they commanded.

169
00:09:33,500 --> 00:09:41,940
[SPEAKER_01] And we were the party who said, no, please leave it up to each citizen to decide how to confront such a health crisis.

170
00:09:41,940 --> 00:09:44,600
[SPEAKER_01] Nobody knew exactly what it was about.

171
00:09:44,600 --> 00:09:49,860
[SPEAKER_01] But it's our conviction that people should be free to decide for themselves.

172
00:09:49,860 --> 00:09:52,679
[SPEAKER_01] So where is Nazism in this thinking?

173
00:09:52,679 --> 00:09:58,299
[SPEAKER_01] The others wanted to make compulsory vaccinations for everyone.

174
00:09:58,299 --> 00:10:01,259
[SPEAKER_01] And we really confronted this in parliament.

175
00:10:01,259 --> 00:10:06,940
[SPEAKER_01] And it was alternative for Germany, together with millions of Germans who took out to the streets,

176
00:10:06,940 --> 00:10:09,860
[SPEAKER_01] who fought this law.

177
00:10:09,860 --> 00:10:14,659
[SPEAKER_01] And so there is no parallel to Hitler's regime.

178
00:10:14,659 --> 00:10:16,779
[SPEAKER_01] We find it evil.

179
00:10:16,779 --> 00:10:19,740
[SPEAKER_01] We say it has destroyed Germany.

180
00:10:19,740 --> 00:10:24,259
[SPEAKER_01] It has not made Germany great, but it has destroyed Germany.

